Ferdinand Bote's death comes a day after the controversial mayor of Tanauan City, Antonio Halili, was shot dead by a sniper. CAPE TOWN - A second Philippine mayor has been shot and killed by an unknown gunman. Ferdinand Bote, mayor of the town of General Tinio, was gunned down by a suspect driving a motorcycle on Tuesday. His death comes a day after the controversial mayor of Tanauan City, Antonio Halili, was shot dead by a sniper. Halili was shot in the chest by an unknown assailant during a flag-raising ceremony at Tanauan City Hall on Monday. Halili conceptualised the so-called walk of shame that saw suspected criminals parade through the city.